	   <tr><td colspan=2>A reliable source for what?&nbsp;&nbsp;That Agility not only affects how fast you raise defensive skills but the probability of getting hit?  Ok, so you don't like the Prima guide.  How about this one: the manual Verant sold me when I bought the game, EverQuest: The Ruins of Kunark, page 27:<br><br>     Agility.  Physical ability; affects your<br>               PROBABILITY (emphasis mine) of<br>               being hit in combat, how much<br>               damage you take per hit, and<br>               how fast you learn some skills.<br><br>Now, if you want to assail this source also, I won't know what to say, but I'll understand. After all, we all know what a reliable source of information Verant has been. (Hold onto your loincloths--just kidding.)<br><br><br><br>    <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
